        dc:description           "FIGURES 12–16. Geographic localization of Coarazuphium pains. 12. Localization of the Karst regions of Arcos, Pains, and Doresópolis in the state of Minas Gerais, Brazil; The grey area corresponds to the Bambui limestone group and the dots correspond to C. pains type localities; 13. Coarazuphium pains, living specimen; 14. Cave type localities, red triangle: cave locality of the holotype lost, yellow: neotype locality, orange: paraneotype I cave locality and blue: other specimen locality; 15. Água Limpa III Cave entrance area; 16. Main conduit from Zé Serafim I Cave. (Photographs 13, 15 and 16 are from Robson de Almeida Zampaulo)." ;
